# AI orchestration / internal process scaffolding — kept locally to drive the
# engineering process, deliberately not published to the public repo: these files
# explicitly describe an LLM roleplaying an engineering org (and, for PROGRESS.md,
# log that roleplay session by session), which would undercut the impression the
# repo is meant to give. They still work locally (Claude Code reads them from disk
# regardless of git tracking) — cloning this repo elsewhere just won't carry them
# along, and status/process claims in the public README are worded accordingly.
# NOTE: docs/ itself is intentionally NOT excluded — the Stage 1-10 documentation,
# ADRs, and sub-stage READMEs are the actual deliverable this project's process is
# meant to demonstrate; only the roleplay/log meta-files above are hidden.
MASTER_PROMPT.md
CLAUDE.md
PROGRESS.md

# Personal, Russian-language step-by-step journal for the user — not for publication.
ЖУРНАЛ_РАЗРАБОТКИ.md

